text: Edythe Amy Macready known as Dot and married name Fairbairn (1908–1994) was a Jersey female diver who competed for England. ==Diving career== Macready trained in the Havre des Pas Pool and won a gold medal in the 10 Metres Platform at the 1934 British Empire Games in London. Dot was the English ladies champion in 1933. ==References== Category:1908 births Category:1994 deaths Category:English female divers Category:English sportswomen Category:Jersey athletes Category:Jersey sportswomen Category:Divers at the 1934 British Empire Games Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in diving Category:Commonwealth Games gold medallists for England
